"title": "8844: unforgiveness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8844",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God remains unforgiving to those described as unrepentant, who blaspheme against the Holy Spirit and who are themselves unforgiving. Being unforgiving and demonstrating true love are mutually exclusive.</p>\n<h2>The unforgiveness of God</h2>\n<h3>Towards the unrepentant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:18-Deut29:21\">DEU 29:18–29:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:21\">EXO 23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:7\">EXO 34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:18\">NUM 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:19\">JOS 24:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:4\">2KI 24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:12-Isa30:14\">ISA 30:12–30:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:7\">JER 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:42\">LAM 3:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:6\">HOS 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:10-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:10–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:28-Heb10:31\">HEB 10:28–10:31</a></p>\n<h3>Towards those whose hearts are hardened</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:20\">JOS 11:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:13-Matt13:15\">MAT 13:13–13:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:11-Mark4:12\">MRK 4:11–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:9-Luke8:10\">LUK 8:9–8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:9–6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:39-John9:41\">JHN 9:39–9:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:23\">JHN 20:23</a></p>\n<h3>Towards those who blaspheme against the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:31-Matt12:32\">MAT 12:31–12:32</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:28-Mark3:29\">MRK 3:28–3:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:10\">LUK 12:10</a> <em>Blasphemy against the Spirit probably involves attributing the authenticating miracles of Jesus Christ to the work of Satan rather than to the power of the Holy Spirit.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:16\">1JN 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Towards those who are not forgiving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:14-Matt6:15\">MAT 6:14–6:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:12-Jas2:13\">JAS 2:12–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:23-Matt5:24\">MAT 5:23–5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:1-Matt7:2\">MAT 7:1–7:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:37-Luke6:38\">LUK 6:37–6:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:32-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:32–18:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23\">MAT 23:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:25-Mark11:26\">MRK 11:25–11:26</a> <em>NIV footnote at verse 26</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:9-Rom14:13\">ROM 14:9–14:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's people call upon him not to forgive the wicked</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:23\">JER 18:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:5\">NEH 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:9\">ISA 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>True love is forgiving</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8\">ROM 5:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:4-1Cor13:5\">1CO 13:4–13:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:5\">PSA 86:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:3-Ps130:4\">PSA 130:3–130:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:9\">DAN 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:18\">MIC 7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:38\">ACT 13:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:7\">ROM 15:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:5-2Cor2:11\">2CO 2:5–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a></p>",
